label: RAS+iL
comment: Finds a solo Remote Access Service (one providing access to the shell on its Host), and adds an isLnS self-referential link so the Service can be selectivly included or excluded in later patterns.

label: SP+iP
comment: Finds a solo reverse proxy process, and adds an isProxy self-referential link so the process can be selectivly included or excluded in later patterns.

label: CucS+iP
comment: Finds a client accessing and being controlled by a service, and adds an isProxy self-referential link so the process can be selectivly included or excluded in later patterns.

label: HuPCH+i
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a Process that is not a Remote Access Service on an Interactive Host, and creates a link specifying that they are also interacting with its Host.

label: HuoH-m+m
comment: Finds any unmanaged Host operated by a Human, and inserts a link specifying the Human is also its manager.

label: HuiPH-Hu+m
comment: Finds a Human interacting with an unmanaged Personal Host, and makes the Human its manager.

label: HuiHP-m+m
comment: Finds a user of an unmanaged interactive process and makes the user the manager of the process.

label: DCH+l
comment: Finds a Physical Host resourced by a Data Centre, and adds the fact that the Host is located in the Data Centre. This is a workaround for an SSM bug that prevented resourcedBy being detected as a case of locatedIn.

label: SHuPH-Hu+m
comment: Makes the Human managing a Space the manager of any unmanaged fixed host within the Space.

label: HurTh-S-m+m
comment: Finds a Thing relating to a Human with no Manager and no specified location, and makes the Human its manager.

label: SHuTh-Hu+m
comment: Makes the Human managing a Space the manager of any unmanaged IoT Thing within the Space.

label: HumPH-m+m
comment: Finds an unmanaged host running a process that has a manager, and makes the process (service) manager the manager of the host.

label: HuiHBTTH-Hu+m
comment: Finds a TrivialHost with no manager, paired via Bluetooth with another host used by a Human, and makes that Human the manager of the TrivialHost.

label: HuiHUSBTH-Hu+m
comment: Finds a TrivialHost with no manager, paired via USB with another host used by a Human, and makes that Human the manager of the TrivialHost.

label: HumHBTTH-Hu+m
comment: Finds a TrivialHost with no manager, paired via Bluetooth with another host managed by a Human, and makes that Human manager of the TrivialHost.

label: HumHUSBTH-Hu+m
comment: Finds a TrivialHost with no manager, paired via USB with another host managed by a Human, and makes that Human manager of the TrivialHost.

label: HuiH-Hu+m
comment: Finds a Human interacting with an unmanaged Host, and makes the Human its manager.

label: Hui2H+iD
comment: Finds a physical Host with two distinct interactive users, and adds a link labelling it as an impersonal host.

label: HuiPH-iD+iP
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a Personal Host, where there is no self-referential link indicating that the device is shared with other users, and adds a self-referential link indicating that this is a personal device.

label: PPS-E+W
comment: Finds a Private Space that is not accessible from any other Space, and makes it accessible from the World.

label: HumTHS+cA
comment: Finds a Human managing a Trivial Host located in a space, and adds a link specifying that the human must have access to the space.

label: HuiHS+cA
comment: Finds a Human that interacts with a Host located in a Space, adds that they must have access to the Space.

label: HuaSaE+cA
comment: Finds a human with access to a space that has an entrance from a public space, and asserts that the human can also access the entrance space.

label: HuiThaS-S+r
comment: Finds a Human that has access to a space and uses an IoT Thing which has no asserted location, and adds a link saying that the device relates to the Human.

label: HuiPDaS-S+l
comment: Finds a Human that has access to a space and uses a personal device which has no asserted location, and adds a link saying that the device may be located in the space accessed by the Human.

label: HBTTHS-S+l
comment: Finds a Host in a Space that accepts pairing via Bluetooth with a TrivialHost that has no location, and adds a link saying the Trivial Host can be in the same space.

label: HUSBTHS-S+l
comment: Finds a Host in a Space that accepts pairing via USB with a TrivialHost that has no location, and adds a link saying the Trivial Host can be in the same space.

label: PH-S+W
comment: Finds a physical host that is not located in any space, and specifies that it is located in the World.

label: C+iC
comment: Finds a Host that represents a Cluster, and marks it as such by adding a self-referential link.

label: EH+iS
comment: Finds a (virtual) Host that is scalable (replicable), and marks it as such by adding a self-referential link.

label: Ct+iC
comment: Finds a solo Container, and adds a self-referential link marking it as such.

label: PodMP+iP
comment: Finds a solo Pod, and adds a self-referential link marking it as such.

label: DC-R+RW
comment: Finds a Data Centre without its own Router, and adds the Router and WiredLAN to the Data Centre, plus a link from the Data Centre manager (if any).

label: DC-C+C
comment: Finds a Data Centre with no server cluster, and adds one.

label: SHuPH-Hu+m-Replay1
comment: Makes the Human managing a Space the manager of any unmanaged fixed host within the Space. This is a repeat of a previous pattern designed to add relationships consequent on other inferred elements since the original pattern was applied.

label: DCWH-LS+c
comment: Finds a Data Centre with its Router and Wired LAN, in which is located another distinct Host not connected to or providing any subnet, and connects this host to the Data Centre wired LAN.

label: DCLS+RWS
comment: Finds each connection from a DataCentre to an Abstract Subnet, and adds the relationship with its internal router.

label: DCVHC+p
comment: Finds a Virtual Host provisioned by a Data Centre but not yet by any host, and adds relationships to the Data Centre cluster.

label: HVH-a+a
comment: Finds a virtual host provisioned by another host and inserts a relationship indicating which is higher up the virtualisation stack.

label: VH2H-a+a
comment: Finds three hosts with relationships indicating they are related in the virtualisation stack, and adds a relationship connecting the highest to the lowest.

label: PH+hPH
comment: Finds a solo physical host and marks it as its own physical host.

label: VHPH+hPH
comment: Finds a VirtualHost that is above a Physical Host in the virtualisation stack, and adds a hasPhysicalHost link between them.

label: DCPS-Pod+Pod
comment: Finds a serverless Process hosted directly on a data centre but not via a Pod, and adds a Pod managed by the Data Centre to contain the Process.

label: DCCt-Pod+Pod
comment: Finds a Container managed directly by a Data Centre and not via a Pod, and inserts the missing Pod.

label: PodP-Cn+Cn
comment: Finds a Pod containing a Process, and inserts a Container for the Process.

label: PodCnP+c
comment: Finds a Process hosted by a Container provisioned by a Pod, and ensures there is a contains relationship between the Pod and the Process.

label: PodCnD+s
comment: Finds Data stored on a Container provisioned by a Pod, and makes the Pod store the Data.

label: PodCnPD+s
comment: Finds a Container running a Process that handles Data stored on the associated Pod, and adds a link to say the Container stores the data. Since the Pod already stores the data, this link means a service on the Pod (or possibly its host) is used to provide a data volume accessed as local storage from the Container.

label: DCPHM+p
comment: Finds a K8s Master whose physical host is in a Data Centre, and asserts that it is managed by the data centre.

label: DCPHW+p
comment: Finds a K8s Worker whose physical host is in a Data Centre, and asserts that it is managed by the data centre.

label: PodDCC-M+M
comment: Finds a Pod managed by a Data Centre that has a Cluster, but there is no Cloud Master node provisioned on the Cluster, and adds the Cloud Master.

label: PodDCMC-W-H+W
comment: Finds a K8s Pod with no Host managed by a Data Centre that has a Cluster with a K8s Master, where the Data Centre does not yet have a K8s Worker cluster, and adds one to host the Pod.

label: PodHaH+a
comment: Finds a Pod provisioned by a Host that is above another Host, and asserts that the Pod is also above the second Host.

label: PodHhPH+hPH
comment: Finds a Pod provisioned by a Host that has a PhysicalHost, and asserts that the Pod has the same PhysicalHost.

label: CtHaH+a
comment: Finds a Container provisioned by a Host that is above another Host, and asserts that the Container is also above the second Host.

label: CtHhPH+hPH
comment: Finds a Container provisioned by a Host that has a PhysicalHost, and assets that the Container has the same PhysicalHost.

label: DCMW-LS+VX
comment: Finds a K8s Master and Worker on the same (cluster) Host in a Data Centre, where the Master and Worker are not on any common subnet, and adds a VXLAN for this provided by the Data Centre.

label: MWHLS+CIP
comment: Finds K8s Master and Worker nodes on the same (cluster) host, and connected to the same subnet, and adds an ClusterIP overlay network to which the Master is connected.

label: MWPodLS2+c
comment: Finds a Pod running on a K8s Worker connected via a Logical Subnet to a K8s Master, which can also access an overlay on the Logical Subnet, and connects the Pod to the overlay subnet.

label: DCCM-A+A
comment: Finds a Data Centre with a Cluster on which is provisioned a Pod management Master node that is not hosting a Pod management API Server, and adds one.

label: DCCM-P+P
comment: Finds a Data Centre with a Cluster on which is provisioned a Pod management Master node that is not hosting a Pod management Ingress reverse proxy, and adds one.

label: DCCMCAP+c
comment: Finds a process controlling a data centre hosting a K8s master node running a K8s API server and Ingress proxy, and adds control links from the process to the two services.

label: VHHsD-HsS-S+S
comment: Finds a Virtual Host above another Host in a virtualisation stack where both store the same Data, there is no lower level host in the stack that also stores the data, and the second host does not run a Process that serves the Data, and adds such a service.

label: VHPhDHS-HsS-S+u
comment: Finds a Virtual Host running a Process that handles Data but does not access it via a service, where its host is in a virtualisation stack above a second Host running a service for the Data, and there is no host between the two in the virtualisation stack running a Process that Serves the Data. Adds a link specifying the the Process uses the data service on the second Host.

label: DCVHRS-H+p
comment: Finds a Host that is physically in a DataCentre and connected to a WiFi LAN that is not provided by any host, and makes the DataCentre provider of the WiFi LAN.

label: DCVHVS-H+p
comment: Finds a Host that is physically in a DataCentre and connected to a virtual subnet that is not provided by any host, and makes the DataCentre provider of the virtual subnet.

label: DCVHWS-H+p
comment: Finds a Host that is physically in a DataCentre and connected to a wired LAN that is not provided by any host, and makes the DataCentre provider of the wired LAN.

label: DCCVH-LS+LS
comment: Finds a Data Centre with a Cluster on which is provisioned a Virtual Host that is not connected to any logical subnet, and adds a virtual subnet provided by the Data Centre to enabled access.

label: DCpLS+RWS
comment: Finds each LogicalSubnet provided by a Data Centre, and adds the relationship with its internal router.

label: HVHS+VS
comment: Finds a virtual host provisioned by another host in a physical location, and adds a HostLAN providing connectivity to the virtual host, provided by its host, and accessible in that location.

label: HumPC-Hu+m
comment: Finds an unmanaged Container of a Process managed by a Human, and makes the Human manager also of the Container.

label: HumHVH-Hu+m
comment: Finds an unmanaged VirtualHost provisioned at a Host managed by a Human, and makes the Human manager also of the Virtual Host.

label: Hc-pN-hP+AC
comment: Finds a Host connected to but not providing an Abstract Subnet, which controlled by a Process not running on the Host, and adds an authentication client on the host which uses the process.

label: HuiHAC+i
comment: Adds the interaction between a human and an authentication client running on their client device.

label: HuiHRAC+i
comment: Adds the interaction between a human and a remote access client running on their client device.

label: PC-LnS+LnS
comment: Adds a login service to a physical cluster if not already present.

label: Rr-LnS+LnS
comment: Adds a login service to a headless Router without one.

label: Sv-LnS+LnS
comment: Adds a login service to a headless Server without one.

label: VH-LnS+LnS
comment: Adds a login service to a headless Virtual Host without one.

label: Hum-iSH-LnS+LnS
comment: Finds a Human managing but not interacting with a Shell Host, where there is no process controlling the host, and adds a login service to allow remote management.

label: Pc-hSHLnS+c
comment: Finds a Process controlling a Shell Host that runs a Remote Access Service, but the Shell Host is not a Pod and not the Process host, and adds a link specifying that the Process controls the RAS.

label: Hum-iHRAS+i
comment: Finds a human managing but not interacting with a host that is not a Pod and has a root privileged remote access service, and adds a link to say the human interacts with the desktop service.

label: HuiCHDtS-AC+AC
comment: Finds a human managing but not interacting directly with a host that has a desktop service, and interacting with a console host but not with a client of the desktop service. Adds a Remote Desktop client enabling remote access to manage the host.

label: HuiCHLnS-AC+AC
comment: Finds a human managing but not interacting directly with a host that has a login service, and interacting with a console host but not with a client of the login service. Adds a Remote Terminal client enabling remote access to manage the host.

label: Co+cD
comment: Finds each IoT Controller device and adds the onboard control input data.

label: Se+cD
comment: Finds each IoT Sensor device and adds the onboard control input data.

label: Se+sD
comment: Finds each IoT Sensor device and adds the sensed output data.

label: SesD+SP
comment: Finds each IoT Sensor device and its sensed Data, and adds an onboard communication process that creates the Data.

label: DcTh+DS
comment: Finds each IoT Thing device and its control input Data, and adds an onboard communication process that serves the Data.

label: Pa-uCo+Rel
comment: Finds a client Process that amends an IoT Controller, and adds relationships between the client and the onboard communication Process and control input Data.

label: PuCo+Rel
comment: Finds a client Process that updates an IoT Controller, and adds relationships between the client and the onboard communication Process and Data.

label: PcSe+Rel
comment: Finds a client Process that alters control input to an IoT Sensor, along with its onboard simple communication Process and Data, and adds relationships between the client and the onboard simple communication Process and Data.

label: PrSe+Rel
comment: Finds an IoT Sensor sending data to a (not really client) Process, and adds a relationship between the onboard simple IoT communication Process and the client Process.

label: Pp-uSe+Rel
comment: Finds a client Process that polls (but does not read) an IoT Sensor to obtain data, and adds relationships between the client and the onboard simple communication Process and Data.

label: PuSe+Rel
comment: Finds a client Process that reads data from an IoT Sensor, and adds relationships between the client and the onboard simple communication Process and Data.

label: HuiCo+UI
comment: Finds the control input for an IoT Controller, which is being used interactively by a Human, and adds a user interface process, plus relationships of the Human to this process and to the input.

label: HuiSe+Rel
comment: Finds the control input and sensed output for an IoT Sensor, which is being used interactively by a Human, plus the interactive process that creates the output, and adds relationships of the Human to the process and data.

label: HurSesD+Rel
comment: Finds Data produced as output by a Sensor related to a Human, and adds the relationship of the Data to the Human.

label: HurThcD+Rel
comment: Finds control input to an IoT Thing related to a Human, and adds the relationship of the Data to the Human.

label: HumThP-m+m
comment: Finds a Human managing a Thing with an unmanaged onboard process, and makes the manager also manage the process.

label: USBD-S+S
comment: Finds Data stored on a USB device where there is no local process serving the data or creating it from scratch.

label: UHDpP-S+S
comment: Finds Data stored on a USB Device paired with a USB Host which is running a process using the Data, where the Data is not also stored on the USB Host, and adds a usage link between the process and the onboard data service on the USB device.

label: UHDrP-S+S
comment: Finds Data stored on a USB Device paired with a USB Host that does not also store the data, where the data is used by a Process running on a third distinct host, and inserts a simple service on the USB Host.

label: UHDSrP+u
comment: Finds Data stored on a USB Device paired with a USB Host running a service for the Data, where the data is used by a Process running on some other host that doesn't use any other process capable of providing the data. Adds a link to say the Process uses the Service on the USB Host.

label: KPxMLnSA+uu
comment: Finds a Remote Access Service that runs on and controls a K8s Master node that runs a K8s API Server, connected via a Subnet to a K8s Worker cluster, and used by a client from outside the K8S cluster, and infers access is mediated by the API Server.

label: KPxWLnSA+uu
comment: Finds a Remote Access Service that runs on and controls a K8s Worker node, connected via a Subnet to a Master that runs a K8s API Server, and used by a client from outside the K8S cluster, and infers access is mediated by the API Server.

label: KPxCLnSA+uu
comment: Finds a Pod managed by K8S or equivalent, hosting a remote access service running in and controlling a Container, and used by a client from outside the K8S cluster, and infers access is mediated by the API Server.

label: KPyMLnSA+aa
comment: Finds a Remote Access Service that runs on and controls a K8s Master node that runs a K8s API Server, connected via a Subnet to a K8s Worker cluster, and used for authentication by a client from outside the K8S cluster, and infers access is mediated by the API Server.

label: KPyWLnSA+aa
comment: Finds a Remote Access Service that runs on and controls a K8s Worker node, connected via a Subnet to a Master that runs a K8s API Server, and used for authentication by a client from outside the K8S cluster, and infers access is mediated by the API Server.

label: KPyCLnSA+aa
comment: Finds a Pod managed by K8S or equivalent, hosting a remote access service running in and controlling a Container, and used for authentication by a client from outside the K8S cluster, and infers access is mediated by the API Server.

label: KPxCaSI+aa
comment: Finds a Pod managed by K8S or equivalent, hosting an unprivileged service in a Container, accessed for authentication purposes by a client from outside the K8S cluster, and infers access is mediated by the Ingress proxy.

label: KPxCuSI+uu
comment: Finds a Pod managed by K8S or equivalent, hosting an unprivileged service in a Container, accessed by a client from outside the K8S cluster, and infers access is mediated by the Ingress proxy.

label: KPxCuScP+aa
comment: Finds a Pod managed by K8S or equivalent, hosting an unprivileged service in a Container, which controls another service accessed by a client from outside the K8S cluster, and infers access by the client to the controlling service is mediated by the Ingress proxy.

label: KIP-S+c
comment: Finds an Ingress proxy mediating access to a service, but not controlled by any other process, and makes it delegate authentication to the back end service (the service controls the Ingress proxy).

label: RTuRAS+uR
comment: Finds a remote terminal client using a remote access service, and adds an inferred link specifying that the client has remote access to the service.

label: RTuCP+uR
comment: Finds a remote terminal client using a console-accessible process, and adds an inferred link specifying that the client has remote access to the process.

label: RTuSP+uR
comment: Finds a remote terminal client using a specialised reverse proxy process, and adds an inferred link specifying that the client has remote access to the proxy.

label: RTuPucS+uR
comment: Finds a remote terminal using an authentication proxy (i.e. the proxy forwards credentials), which in turn uses and is controlled by a service, and adds an inferred link specifying that the client has remote access to the proxy.

label: RDuP-LnS+uR
comment: Finds a remote desktop client using a process that is not a login service, and adds an inferred link specifying that the client has remote access to the process.

label: RDuDtS+uR
comment: Finds a remote desktop client using a desktop service, and adds an inferred link specifying that the client has remote access to the service.

label: RDuDtSuPH+uR
comment: Finds a remote desktop service using a process on the same host, and used by a remote desktop client, and infers that the client can also remotely access the process.

label: RTuRASuCPH+uR
comment: Finds a remote access service using a console process on the same host, and used by a remote terminal client, adds an inferred link specifying that the client can also remotely access the console process.

label: CucS+uR
comment: Finds a client accessing and being controlled by a service, and adds a link to specify that the client can access the service remotely.

label: SPuS+uR
comment: Finds a reverse proxy directly using a service, and adds a link to specify that the proxy can access the service remotely.

label: PurRASuSH+uR
comment: Finds a process acting as a reverse proxy, which can remotely use a remote access service that uses a collocated process, and adds a link to say the proxy can remotely use that process.

label: RACuPuP-uR+uR
comment: Finds a remote access client remotely using a proxy which remotely uses another proxy, where there is as yet no link specifying that the client can remotely access the second proxy, and fills in the link.

label: RTuPuRAS+uR
comment: Finds a remote terminal remotely using a proxy which remotely uses a remote access service, and adds a link to specify that the remote terminal can remotely access the login service.

label: RTuPuCP+uR
comment: Finds a remote terminal remotely using a proxy which remotely uses a console process, and adds a link to specify that the remote terminal can remotely access the console process.

label: RDuPuS-LnS+uR
comment: Finds a remote desktop remotely using a proxy that remotely uses a process that is not a login service, and adds a link to specify that the remote desktop can remotely access the process.

label: RDuPuDtS+uR
comment: Finds a remote desktop remotely using a proxy that remotely uses a desktop service, and adds an inferred link specifying that the client has remote access to the process.

label: RDuRDuS-uR+uR
comment: Finds a remote desktop using remotely another remote desktop which is using remotely a third process that is not yet remotely used by the first, adds a link specifying that the third process is used by the first.

label: RTuRTuS-uR+uR
comment: Finds a remote terminal using remotely another remote terminal which is using remotely a third process that is not yet remotely used by the first, adds a link specifying that the third process is used by the first.

label: RDuRTuS-uR+uR
comment: Finds a remote desktop using remotely a remote terminal which is using remotely a third process that is not yet remotely used by the first, adds a link specifying that the third process is used by the first.

label: HuRACP+i
comment: Finds a human interacting with a remote access client on a local host that is remotely using a process that is not a proxy, adds a link specifying that the human can interact remotely with the process.

label: HuRDuPH-DtS+DtS
comment: Finds a Human interacting via a Remote Desktop client with a Process that is not a remote access service, running on a Host that lacks a Desktop Service used by the same Human, and where the Remote Desktop is the last remote access client in the chain between the Human and the Process, and adds the missing Desktop Service collocated with and controlling the remote Process.

label: HuRTuCPH-LnS+LnS
comment: Finds a Human interacting via a Remote Terminal client with a Process that is not a remote access service, running on a Host that lacks a Login Service used by the same Human, adds the missing Login Service.

label: HuRDRASPH+c
comment: Finds a Human interacting via a Remote Desktop with a Process that is not a Remote Access Service, and a collocated Remote Access Service, and infers that the Remote Access Client remotely uses the Remote Access Service which uses the Process.

label: HuRTRASCPH+c
comment: Finds a Human interacting via a Remote Terminal with a Console Process that is not a Remote Access Service, and a collocated Remote Access Service, and infers that the Remote Access Client remotely uses the Remote Access Service which uses the Process.

label: HRAScScP+ca
comment: Finds a process acting as a back end service, accessed by (and controlling) an authentication proxy, and used by a remote access service running on the same host, and infers that the proxy also uses and is controlled by the remote access service.

label: HRAScSuSP+a
comment: Finds a process acting as a back end service, accessed by an authenticating proxy, and used by a remote access service running on the same host, infers that the proxy also uses the remote access service.

label: HRASuSC+uRAS
comment: Finds a Client using a Process via a Remote Access Service on the same Host, and adds link from the Client to the Process marking it as an indirect access.

label: HuCurHRASuP+uR
comment: Finds a Human using a Remote Access Client to access a Process via a collocated Remote Access Service. Adds a link specifying that the Remote Access Service remotely uses the Process.

label: HuCurHRASuPurS+uR
comment: Finds a Human using a Remote Access Client to access a Service via a Remote Access Service and collocated Process. Adds a link specifying that the Remote Access Service remotely uses the Process.

label: CurPuRASurS+uR
comment: Finds a remote access client accessing a service via a remote access service which itself is accessed via a proxy. Adds a link specifying that the proxy uses the service remotely.

label: CurPuPurS+uR
comment: Finds a remote access client accessing a service via a proxy which itself is accessed via a proxy. Adds a link specifying that the proxy uses the service remotely. Applied iteratively.

label: CucSaP+c
comment: Finds a process acting as an authentication proxy to a second process, and also using a third process for authN which controls the second, and adds a link to specify that the first process is acting as an authN proxy for the authenticator.

label: CucS+N
comment: Finds a process acting as an authentication proxy to a second process, i.e. the first process acceses the second and the second controls the first. Adds a link to say that the first process authenticates as a proxy to the second.

label: PnPnS-U+U
comment: Finds a client using a service via an authentication proxy (i.e. the proxy forwards credentials), and there is no link yet indicating indirect usage. At this stage in the construction sequence, the client itself will also be an authentication proxy. Adds links for indirect usage without authentcation.

label: CuPnS-U+U
comment: Finds a client using an authentication proxy (i.e. the proxy forwards credentials), which in turn uses a service, and there is no link saying the client is indirectly using the service. Adds this link, plus a link to specify that the proxy does not authenticate the client.

label: SPu-nS-U+U
comment: Finds a reverse proxy directly using and authenticating with a service, and adds a link marking the relationship as service use as a proxy.

label: SPv-nS-U+U
comment: Finds a reverse proxy using and authenticating with a service via a chain of authentication proxies, and adds a link marking the relationship as service use as a proxy.

label: SPvSPvS-U+U
comment: Finds a reverse proxy using a second reverse proxy that uses a service, with mutual authentication at each step, and with no link indicating that the first proxy is indirectly using the third. Adds the missing link.

label: CvSPvS-U+U
comment: Finds a client indirectly using a reverse proxy that uses and authenticates with a service, where the client has as yet no link indicating that the client is indirectly using the service. Adds the missing link, and a link indicating that the client does authenticate with the proxy.

label: CuSPvS-U+U
comment: Finds a client directly using a reverse proxy that uses and authenticates with a service, where the client has as yet no link indicating that the client is indirectly using the service. Adds the missing link, and a link indicating that the client does authenticate with the proxy.

label: HuSP+SMS
comment: Finds a human user interacting with a smartphone which is a personal device with no other users, and adds an SMS client used by that user.

label: HHuWSMS+D
comment: Adds a (spam) data dependency between a web browser and SMS client used by someone on the same host.

label: HHuWE+D
comment: Adds a (spam) data dependency between a web browser and email client used by someone on the same host.

label: HuWES+D
comment: Adds a (spam) data dependency between a web browser and an email service it accesses.

label: TP+iT
comment: Finds a solo trivial process, and adds an isTrivial self-referential link so the process can be selectivly included or excluded in later patterns.

label: AC+noDX
comment: Finds a solo AuthClient, and adds a self referential link indicating the process cannot exchange data.

label: AS+noDX
comment: Finds a solo authentication/authorisation service, and adds a self referential link indicating the process cannot exchange data.

label: RAS+noDU
comment: Finds a remote access service, and adds a self referential link indicating the process cannot process data.

label: RAC+noDU
comment: Finds a remote access client, and adds a self referential link indicating the process cannot process data.

label: CS-SP+DX
comment: Finds a client using a service, both of which are able to exchange data, and having at least one service channel indicating they are communicating with each other directly (not via a proxy), and creates a Data Exchange between them.

label: HuRACuPD+pR
comment: Finds Human interacting remotely via a Remote Access Client with a Process that processes Data, and adds a link to specify that the Remote Access Client is involved in remotely processing the Data.

label: HuirEaD+aD
comment: Finds Human interacting remotely with an Editor process that amends data, and adds a link to say that the Human amends the data.

label: HuirIPaD+aD
comment: Finds Human interacting remotely with a process that amends data, and adds a link to say that the Human amends the data.

label: HuaDirPaD-P+eUU
comment: Finds a Human interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that amends Data, where the Human amends that Data, but no process is yet enabling the interaction with the data. Adds a link specifying that the Interactive Process enables the interaction with the Data.

label: HuirEc-rD+iD
comment: Finds a Human interacting (possibly remotely) with an Editor that creates but does not receive Data, and adds a link to specify that the Human enters the data.

label: HuirEr-vD-cC-iHu-DS+iD
comment: Finds Human interacting (possibly remotely) with an Editor that receives Data that is not viewed by the Human, and which is not created by any process, stored on any Host, nor input by any Human, and adds a link specifying that the Human inputs the Data.

label: HuirPr-vD-cC-iHu-DS+iD
comment: Finds Human interacting remotely with a Process that receives Data that is not viewed by the Human, and which is not created by any process, stored on any Host, nor input by any Human, and adds a link specifying that the Human inputs the Data.

label: HuiDirIPpD-P+eUI
comment: Finds a Human interacting (possibly remotely) with an Interactive Process that processes Data, where the Human enters that Data, but no process is yet enabling the interaction with the data, and adds a link to specify this is done by the Interactive Process.

label: HuiDirPpD-P+eUI
comment: Finds a Human interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes Data, where the Human enters that Data, but no process is yet enabling the interaction with the data. Adds a link specifying that the Interactive Process enables the interaction with the Data.

label: HuirEp-iD+vD
comment: Finds a Human interacting (possibly remotely) with an Editor that processes Data, where the Human does not enter that Data, and adds a link specifying that the Human inputs the Data.

label: HuirIPp-iD+vD
comment: Finds Human interacting (possibly remotely) with an Interactive Process that processes Data, where the Human does not enter the Data, and adds a link to say that the Human views the Data.

label: HuirPc-iD-rC-vHu-DS+vD
comment: Finds a Human interacting (possibly remotely) with a process that creates data, where the data is not stored on any host, used by any process nor viewed by any user, and the Human does not enter the Data, and adds a link to specify that the Human views the data.

label: HuirPr-iD-cD+vD
comment: Finds Human interacting remotely with a Process that receives Data, but does not create any output, and the Human does not enter the Data, and adds a link to specify that the Human views the data.

label: HuirPaD+eUI-O+vD
comment: Finds Human interacting (possibly remotely) with a process that amends (creates and receives) data, and enables user input but not output of the data, and adds a link to specify that the Human views the data.

label: HuvDirPrD-P+eUO
comment: Find a Human interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that receives Data, where the Human views that Data, but no process is yet enabling the interaction with the data. Adds a link to say the  Process enables the user output.

label: HuvDirPcD-P+eUO
comment: Find a Human interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that creates Data, where the Human views that Data, but no process is yet enabling the interaction with the data. Adds a link to say the  Process enables the user output.

label: HD-aHD-DS+DS
comment: Adds a stored copy of Data on a Host where the Data is stored, and the Host is not in a virtualisation stack above another Host where the Data is also stored.

label: HPsD-DS+DR
comment: Adds a DataRelay asset where a process serves (but does not process) data that is not stored locally, signifying that this data is forwarded between other processes by this process. Note that this also means the process forwards requests for data, and (if it is a DB asset) may process those requests before forwarding them, e.g. evaluating queries to work out which data to request from the data store.

label: PsDSH-DP+DP
comment: Finds a Process serving (but not processing) locally stored Data, and creates the corresponding Stored Data Pool (local stored copy of this data served by this process).

label: PaDSH-Hu-DP+UP
comment: Finds a Process that is amending data of which there is a copy stored on the same host, where the Process is not enabling a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no Data Pool associated with the Data. Adds an UpdatePool (data update by a non-interactive process which is the only source of the data).

label: HuaDSPH-DP+UP
comment: Finds a Human amending Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is a copy on the same Host, where there is as yet no Data Pool associated with the data. Adds a UserUpdatePool (data updated at an interactive process which is the only source of this data).

label: Pc-rDSH-Hu-DP+OP
comment: Finds a Process that is creating data of which there is a copy stored on the same host, where the Process is not enabling a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no Data Pool associated with the Data. Adds an OutputPool (data creation by a non-interactive process which is the only source of the data).

label: Hui-vDSPH-DP+OP
comment: Finds a Human entering Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is a copy on the same Host, where there is as yet no Data Pool associated with the data. Adds an OutputPool (data generated or provided by the user at a process which is the only source of this data).

label: Pr-cDSH-Hu-DP+IP
comment: Finds a Process that is receiving data of which there is a copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no Data Pool associated with the Data. Adds an InputPool (data used by a non-interactive process which is the only source of the data).

label: PaDH-DS-Hu-DP+UP
comment: Finds a Process that is amending data of which there is no copy stored on the same host, where the Process is not enabling a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data pool anywhere associated with this Data. Adds an UpdatePool (data update by a non-interactive process which is the only source of the data). Note that by this stage, matching data cannot be stored anywhere, so amending the data is a modelling error. However, we need to create the UpdatePool to avoid also creating other (misleading) errors.

label: HuaDPH-DS-DP+UP
comment: Finds a Human amending Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is no copy on the same Host, and as yet no Data Pool anywhere associated with this Data. Adds an UpdatePool (data update by a non-interactive process which is the only source of the data). Note that by this stage, matching data cannot be stored anywhere, so amending the data is a modelling error. However, we need an UpdatePool to avoid also creating other (misleading) errors.

label: Pc-rDH-DS-Hu-DP+OP
comment: Finds a Process that is creating data of which there is no copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no Data Pool associated with the Data. Adds an OutputPool (data creation by a non-interactive process which is the only source of the data).

label: Hui-vDPH-DS-DP+OP
comment: Finds a Human entering Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is no copy on the same Host, where there is as yet no Data Pool associated with the data. Adds an OutputPool.

label: PaDSH-S-Hu-DA+DU
comment: Finds a Process that is amending data of which there is a copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data access associated with this Process and Data, and no Data Pool at this Host associated with the Data. Adds a non-interactive DataUpdate asset.

label: HuaDSPH-S-DA+DU
comment: Finds a Human amending Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is a copy on the same Host, where there is no Data Pool associated with the data at that Host and as yet no Data Access associated with this Process and Data. Adds a DataUpdate (data updated at a process possibly by an interactive user).

label: PaDSH+S-Hu-DA+DU
comment: Finds a Process that is amending data of which there is a copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data access associated with this Process and Data, but there is at least one Data Pool at this Host associated with the Data. Adds a non-interactive DataUpdate asset.

label: HuaDSPH+S-DA+DU
comment: Finds a Human amending Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is a copy on the same Host, where there is a  Data Pool associated with the data at that Host but as yet no Data Access associated with this Process and Data. Adds a Data Update (data updated at a process possibly by an interactive user).

label: PaDH-DS-Hu-DA+DU
comment: Finds a Process that is amending data of which there is no copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data access associated with this Process and Data. Adds a DataUpdate (data update by a non-interactive process).

label: HuaDPH-DS-DA+DU
comment: Finds a Human amending Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is no copy on the same Host, and as yet no Data Access associated with this Process and Data. Adds a DataUpdate (data updated at a process possibly by an interactive user).

label: Pc-rDSH-S-Hu-DA+DO
comment: Finds a Process that is creating data of which there is a copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data access associated with this Process and Data, and no Data Pool at this Host associated with the Data. Adds a DataOutput (data generated at a non-interactive process).

label: Hui-vDSPH-S-DA+DO
comment: Finds a Human entering Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is a copy on the same Host, where there is no Data Pool associated with the data at that Host and as yet no Data Access associated with this Process and Data. Adds a UserInput (data generated possibly by the user at an interactive process).

label: Pc-rDSH+S-Hu-DA+DO
comment: Finds a Process that is creating data of which there is a copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data access associated with this Process and Data, but there is at least one Data Pool at this Host associated with the Data. Adds a DataOutput (data generated at a non-interactive process).

label: Hui-vDSPH+S-DA+DO
comment: Finds a Human entering Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is a copy on the same Host, where there is a Data Pool associated with the data at that Host but as yet no Data Access associated with this Process and Data. Adds a DataOutput (data generated at a process possibly by an interactive user).

label: Pc-rDH-DS-Hu-DA+DO
comment: Finds a Process that is creating data of which there is no copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data access associated with this Process and Data. Adds a DataOutput (data generated at a non-interactive process).

label: Hui-vDPH-DS-DA+DO
comment: Finds a Human entering Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is no copy on the same Host, and there is as yet no Data Access associated with this Process and Data. Adds a DataOutput (data generated at a process possibly by an interactive user).

label: Pr-cDSH-S-Hu-DA+DI
comment: Finds a Process that is receiving data of which there is a copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data access associated with this Process and Data, and no Data Pool at this Host associated with the Data. Adds a DataInput (data consumed at a non-interactive process).

label: Pr-cDSH+S-Hu-DA+DI
comment: Finds a Process that is receiving data of which there is a copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data access associated with this Process and Data, but there is at least one Data Pool at this Host associated with the Data. Adds a DataInput (data consumed at a non-interactive process).

label: Pr-cDH-DS-Hu-DA+DI
comment: Finds a Process that is receiving data of which there is no copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data access associated with this Process and Data. Adds a DataInput (data consumed at a non-interactive process).

label: HuaDRAC-DA+RUA
comment: Finds a Human amending Data remotely via a Remote Access Client, where there is no Data Access asset for access to the Data by the RAC. Adds a Remote User Update asset (data flowing via the Client to and from the Human).

label: DC3-x+x
comment: Finds a Data Channel extending a second Data Channel which extends a third Data Channel, where the first does not yet extend the third. Adds a link to specify that the first Data Channel does extend the third.

label: PSDP+ds
comment: Finds a Process that serves stored Data, and adds links to specify that it is both a source and destination for this Data.

label: PDR+ds
comment: Finds a Process acting as a Data Relay, and adds links to specify that it is both a source and destination for this Data.

label: PDI+d
comment: Finds a Process that uses Data as input, or displays it to an interactive user, and adds a link to specify it is a destination for this Data.

label: PDI-Hu+d
comment: Finds a Process that uses Data as input and does not have an interactive user, and adds a link to specify that it is a source for this Data.

label: PDO+s
comment: Finds a Process that creates Data as output, or gets it from an interactive user, and adds a link to specify that it is a source for this Data.

label: RUIDO+ds
comment: Finds a Process that enables remote user input, and adds link to specify that the remote access client is a source, and the enabling Process a destination for this Data.

label: RUODI+ds
comment: Finds a Process that enables remote user output, and adds link to specify that the remote access client is a destination, and the enabling Process a source for this Data.

label: PDP+DP
comment: Finds a Process that implicitly or explicitly serves stored Data, and creates a Data Path for the Data from the Process.

label: PDO-DI+DP
comment: Finds a Process that creates Data as output, possibly by getting it from an interactive user, but does not use the same Data as input, and creates a Data Path for the Data from the Process.

label: SDADPPDXP-DP+DP
comment: Finds a service with a data access to which there is a data path from a process that exchanges data with a third process which is not the service and from which there is no data path to the same data access. Creates a new Data Path from the third process extending the old one.

label: HSDADPPDXP-Hu-DP+DP
comment: Finds a service with a data access to which there is a data path from a non-interactive process that exchanges data with a third process which is not the service and from which there is no data path to the same data access, where all three processes have the same host. Creates a new Data Path from the third process extending the old one.

label: SDADPPDXP-Hu-DP+DP
comment: Finds a service with a data access to which there is a data path from a non-interactive process that exchanges data with a third process which is not the service and from which there is no data path to the same data access.  Creates a new Data Path from the third process extending the old one.

label: SDADPPDXPRAC-DP+DP
comment: Finds a service with a data access to which there is a data path from a process that exchanges data with a third process which is not the service and from which there is no data path to the same data access, and there is a remote access client using remotely the second and third processes. Creates a new Data Path from the third process extending the old one.

label: SDADPPDXRAC-DP+DP
comment: Finds a service with a data access to which there is a data path from a process that exchanges data with a third process which is not the service and from which there is no data path to the same data access, and there is a remote access client using remotely the second and third processes. Creates a new Data Path from the third process extending the old one.

label: DSDPS+DC
comment: Finds a data path from a process to a service, where the process is a source of the data. Creates a data channel for that data source from the process to the service.

label: DSDCDP2oDD+DC
comment: Finds a Data Source for which there is a Data Channel to a next Process, which uses a Data Path that extends another Data Path to another Process, and where no previously found process is a data destination. Creates a new Data Channel leading up to the old one.

label: DDDPS-DC+DC
comment: Finds a Data Path from a Process that is a Data Destination to a Service, where there is no Data Channel using the Data Path. Creates a Data Channel for the Data Destination from the Process to the Service.

label: DDDCDP2oDS+DC
comment: Finds a Data Desination for which there is an untried Data Channel to a next Process, which uses a Data Path that extends another Data Path to another Process, and where no previously found process is a data source. Creates a new Data Channel leading up to the old one.

label: RA-fDCSDD+ch
comment: Finds a remote access client acting as a data source but not itself getting the data from any original source, and having a data channel to a service that can act as a data destination. Adds links specifying that this is a complete channel from source to destination, and that data flows along the channel.

label: DO-fDCSDD+ch
comment: Finds a data output process that acts as a data source but does not itself get the data from any original source, and having a data channel to a service that can act as a data destination. Adds links specifying that this is a complete channel from source to destination, and that data flows along the channel.

label: DADSDCSDD-f+ch
comment: Finds a data access process that acts as a data source and itself gets the data from an original source, and having a data channel to a service that can act as a data destination that does not receive data from this original source. Adds links specifying that this is a complete channel from source to destination, and that data flows along the channel.

label: DUDSDCSDD+ch
comment: Finds a data access process that acts as a data source and sends data to a data destination where the original source is a data update. Adds links specifying that this is a complete channel in which data flows backwards from the destination to the source.

label: RA-fDCSDS+ch
comment: Finds a remote access client acting as a data destination that is not fulfilled (sent data) by any process, and having a data channel to a service that can act as a data source. Adds links specifying that this is a complete channel from source to destination, and that data flows along the channel.

label: DI-fDCSDS+ch
comment: Finds a process using input and acting as a data destination that is not yet fulfilled (sent data) by any process, and having a data channel to a service that can act as a data source. Adds links specifying that this is a complete channel from source to destination, and that data flows along the channel.

label: DD-fDCSDS+ch
comment: Finds a data access process that acts as a data destination that is not fulfilled by any other process, and has a data channel to a service that can act as a data source. Adds links specifying that this is a complete channel from source to destination, and that data flows along the channel.

label: DADC2DP2S+fwd-ch+ch
comment: Finds a Process with a Data Access having a Data Channel to a Service where data flows forwards along the channel, using a Data Path that extends a second Data Path used by a second Data Channel for the same Data Access, that isn't yet to the Service. Adds links specifying that data flows forwards along the second channel between the two processes.

label: DADC2DP2S+rev-ch+ch
comment: Finds a Process with a Data Access having a Data Channel to a Service where data flows backwards along the channel, using a Data Path that extends a second Data Path used by a second Data Channel for the same Data Access, that isn't yet to the Service. Adds links specifying that data flows backwards along the second channel between the two processes.

label: DDDCDS2P+DF
comment: Finds a Data Channel for a Data Destination, where the channel ends at a Data Source, and the Data Channel is tagged by a reverse link from the Data Destination indicating there is a data flow backwards along the channel, plus the associated source and destination Processes and the Data. Inserts an end-to-end data flow.

label: DSDCDD2P+DF
comment: Finds a Data Channel for a Data Source, where the channel ends at a Data Destination, and the Data Channel is tagged by a forward link from the Data Source indicating there is a data flow forwards along the channel, plus the associated source and destination Processes and the Data. Inserts an end-to-end data flow.

label: DFDCO4P+DFS
comment: Finds a a Data Channel between two processes and carrying a forward Data Flow between the associated source and destination processes. Inserts a Data Step between the two adjacent processes.

label: DFDCI4P+DFS
comment: Finds a a Data Channel between two processes and carrying a reverse Data Flow between the associated source and destination processes. Inserts a Data Step between the two adjacent processes.

label: HPsDPDFDS+f
comment: Finds a Host that stores a copy of Data served by and sent to a Process on the same Host, plus the associated Data Flow and Data Pool, and adds a link to specify that the data access covers writing the stored data.

label: HPsDPDSDF+f
comment: Finds a Host that stores a copy of Data served by and sent from a Process on the same Host, plus the associated Data Flow and Data Pool, and adds a link to specify that the data access covers reading the stored data.

label: HPDS-fDI-DO-DFI+f
comment: Finds a Host with a stored Data Copy, running a Process that has a Data Input asset for the same Data that is not also a Data Output, is not yet fulfilled by the stored Data Copy, nor by an incoming data flow, and there is no collocated DataPool (i.e. no service able to provide supply the data). Adds a link saying that the Data Access is fulfilled by (i.e. reads from) the stored copy of the Data.

label: HPDFDI-fDS-DP+f
comment: Finds a Host with a stored Data Copy, running a Process that has a Data Input asset for the same Data that does not yet fulfil the stored Data Copy, and the Data Input is fulfilled by an incoming Data Flow, but there is no Data Pool for this data and any process on the same Host. Adds a link saying that the Process fulfils (i.e. writes to) the stored copy of the Data.

label: HPDO-fDS-DA+f
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that creates locally stored Data which it produces as output, but where the Data Output asset does not fulfil the stored copy, and is not a source of data for any other Data Access that fulfils the stored copy. This means the process is not sending updates to that stored copy, so links are added specifying that it writes directly to the stored copy..

label: HPDADSDU+crudu
comment: Finds a Host storing a Data Copy fulfilled by a Data Access that sources data from a Data Update (from a process on any Host). Adds a link to specify that the Process is CRUD updating the stored data.

label: HPDADS2dDO+crudu
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that writes to a local stored Data Copy, and sources data from two distinct data producers. Adds a link to specify that the process CRUD updates the data (since it must be overwriting or appending data from one producer when it gets data from another).

label: HPeD+crudu
comment: Finds a Host for a Process that creates and appends to locally stored Data, and asserts a CRUD update relationship from the process to the stored data copy.

label: HPDADS-crudu+crudc
comment: Finds a Host storing a Data Copy fulfilled by a local process that does not CRUD update the data copy, and adds a CRUD creates relationship bewteen process and data copy.

label: HPDSDA-crudr+crudr
comment: Finds a Host storing a Data Copy that fulfils a Data Access for a Process on the same Host, and adds a CRUD read relationship between Process and Data Copy if there is not already a CRUD updates.

label: DUDA-eS+eA
comment: Finds a service controlling access to a data access, which is fulfilled by a data use that is not yet controlled by any process, and makes the service controller of the data use.

label: DADU-eS+eA
comment: Finds a service controlling access to a data access, which fulfils a data use that is not yet controlled by any process, and makes the service controller of the data use.

label: DADS+W
comment: Finds a Data Access fulfilling a Data Copy. Adds a link signifying that the Data Copy can be written to as a consequence of the Data Access.

label: DSDA+R
comment: Finds a Data Access fulfilled by a Data Copy. Adds a link signifying that the Data Copy can be read as a consequence of the Data Access.

label: SDUDADS+W
comment: Finds a Service enabling access for a Data Use, where the Service writes to a local Data Copy. Adds a link signifying that the Data Copy can be written to as a consequence of the Data Use.

label: SDUDSDA+R
comment: Finds a Service enabling access for a Data Use, where the Service reads from a local Data Copy. Adds a link signifying that the Data Copy can be read as a consequence of the Data Use.

label: InternetMP+ii
comment: Finds an Internet class network, and labels it as such using a self-referential link.

label: HL+iH
comment: Finds a solo HostLAN and marks it as such by adding a self-referential relationship. This is used later to exclude HostLAN assets in a construction pattern that refers to a base class.

label: Rr+iR
comment: Finds a solo Router, and labels it as such using a self-referential link.

label: MHC+iMHC
comment: Finds a solo Mobile Console Host, and labels it as such using a self-referential link.

label: WpHS-aF+iH
comment: Finds a mobile host or virtual host running on it, in a space, providing a WiFi LAN which is not accessible from any space, and providing no other WiFiLAN accessible in its space. Adds a link indicating that the first WiFiLAN is an abstract hotspot.

label: InternetMP+W
comment: Finds an Internet class network, and makes it accessible to the World (adding the World if not already present).

label: FpLSS+aF
comment: Finds a Fixed Host located in a Space (or a Virtual Host running on it) and providing a Logical Subnet, adds that the subnet is accessible from that Space.

label: FcLSS+aF
comment: Finds a Fixed Host located in a Space (or a Virtual Host running on it) and connected to a Logical Subnet, adds that the subnet is accessible from that Space.

label: MHcIS+aF
comment: Finds a Mobile Console Host in a Public Space connected to the Internet, and makes the Internet accessible from that space.

label: WS-H+I
comment: Finds a solo WiFiLAN that is not an abstract hotspot, and adds a link to say it is its own local implementation.

label: WpHSH-aF+WH
comment: Finds a mobile host or virtual host running on it providing a WiFi LAN which is a hotspot, a space where the host could be where it has no explicit provision or connection to any other WiFiLAN. In that space it is assumed the host provides a local WiFiLAN hotspot implementation, which is then added to the model.

label: HcWHS+c
comment: Finds a WiFiLAN hotspot and its local implementation in a Space, and a host connected to the hotspot in that space, and adds a connection to the local implementation.

label: PcWH+c
comment: Finds a WiFiLAN and its local implementation, plus a controlling process, and makes the process also controller of the local implementation.

label: PCN+W
comment: Finds a Public Celluler Network, and makes it accessible to the World (adding the World if not already present).

label: FCNS+aF
comment: Finds a Fixed Host located in a Space (or a Virtual Host running on it) and connected to a Cellular Network, adds that the network is accessible from that Space.

label: MPCNS+aF
comment: Finds a Mobile Host located in a Space (or a Virtual Host running on it) that is connected to a Public Cellular Network, and makes that Network accessible from that Space.

label: CN-R+R
comment: Finds a cellular network that is not provided by a router, and adds one.

label: PCNRWI+ct
comment: Finds router providing a Public Cellular Network accessible from the World, along with the Internet which should also be accessible from the World, and connects the router to the Internet.

label: CNR+CN
comment: Finds a cellular network provided by a router an adds a core network. Note that the inferred core network is not accessible from any space: this ensures that routing segments are not added by the default patterns, so they can be customised to reflect default cellular network behaviour.

label: CNHS+AN
comment: Finds a core network implementing a cellular network accessible from a space in which there is a device connected to but not providing the cellular network. Adds a base station and a radio access network in the space, and connects the device to them.

label: PcCN+c
comment: Finds a process controlling a cellular network and an associated RAN, and adds a link saying the process controls the RAN.

label: RrBcC+NSg
comment: Finds a BaseStation providing a RAN and connected to a core network both of which are part of a cellular network, and adds a NAT Segment from the former to the latter subnet.

label: CcBrR+CSg
comment: Finds a Base Station connected to a backhaul Core Network and providing a RAN, both of which are part of a Cellular Network, and adds a closed segment indicating that routing requests into a cell is not supported for a cellular network.

label: L3cCrC+OSg
comment: Finds a core router providing a core network backhaul for a cellular network, connected to an IP subnet that is not part of the cellular network, and adds an open segment routing connections from the former to the latter.

label: CrCcL3+NSg
comment: Finds a core router providing a core network backhaul for a cellular network, connected to an IP subnet that is not part of the cellular network, and adds a NAT segment routing connections from the former to the latter.

label: HpBRH+B
comment: Finds pairs of Physical Hosts paired over Bluetooth and adds the Bluetooth radio subnet created between them.

label: HpURH+U
comment: Finds pairs of Physical Hosts paired over USB and adds the USB wired connection created between them.

label: CuSHS+SL
comment: Finds a Host that is not a Cluster running both a Client and a Service used by the Client, in a Space, and adds an internal subnet representing internal (socket or API) connectivity within the Host.

label: HprLS+c
comment: Adds a connection from a gateway Host to a LogicalSubnet provided by that Host, unless it is an abstract hotspot.

label: HLS+I
comment: Adds an Interface between a Host and a LogicalSubnet it is connected to, unless the subnet is a hotspot.

label: ILSA+c
comment: Finds an Interface to a Logical Subnet that implements an Abstract Subnet, and makes the Interface also connect to the Abstract Subnet.

label: L3c-rGc-rL3+OSg
comment: Finds a Host connected from an IP subnet to a second distinct IP subnet, both in the same space, where neither is a hotspot and neither is provided by the gateway, and adds an Open Segment from the former to the latter subnet.

label: L3c-rGrL3+DSg
comment: Finds a Host connected from an IP subnet it does not provide to a second, distinct IP subnet that is provided by the Host, both in the same space, where neither subnet is a hotspot. Adds a DeNat Segment (public to private) from the former to the latter subnet.

label: L3rGc-rL3+NSg
comment: Finds a Host connected from an IP subnet to a distinct IP subnet, the former but not the latter being provided by the Host, and both in the same space, and adds a NAT Segment from the former to the latter subnet.

label: L3rGrL3+OSg
comment: Finds a Host providing two distinct IP subnets both in the same space, and adds an Open Segment from one to the other.

label: L1c-rGcL3+NSg
comment: Finds a physical host with a pairing connection from a distinct host that is also connected to an IP subnet, all in the same space, and adds a reverse tethering segment from the paired host to the IP subnet.

label: L1rGcL3+OSg
comment: Finds a Bluetooth or USB device connected from a host to an IP subnet, all in the same space, and adds an Open Segment from the former to the latter. Here the gateway is a Bluetooth or USB device, so this corresponds to a regular tethering connection.

label: L3cGc-rL1+CSg
comment: Finds a Physical Host gateway on an IP subnet with a connection from a USB or Bluetooth device, all in the same space, and adds a Closed Segment from the former to the latter subnet. The Bluetooth or USB device is not acting as the gateway, so this corresponds to a reverse tethering connection in the wrong direction for message routing to take place.

label: L3cGrL1+OSg
comment: Finds a USB/Bluetooth device acting as a gateway, connected to an IP subnet and paired with a host in the same space, and adds an Open Segment from the former to the latter subnet. This configuration corresponds to a regular tethering connection allowing communication from the IP subnet to the USB/Bluetooth host.

label: UPc-rGrUP+OSg
comment: Finds a USB hub between a USB device and a USB host (it provides the USB Pair from the USB Host, but not to the USB device), and adds a segment from the USB host to the USB device.

label: UPrGc-rUP+OSg
comment: Finds a USB hub between a USB host and a USB device (it provides the USB Pair from the USB Host, but not to the USB device), and adds a segment from the USB host to the USB device.

label: BPcGcBP+OSg
comment: Finds a Bluetooth device paired with two other devices, and adds a logical segment representing the route between bluetooth connections which corresponds to Bluetooth mesh routing.

label: SgHfILS+f
comment: Adds a relationship between a Logical Segment and the Interface between its gateway Host and the Logical Subnet it routes from.

label: SgHtILS+t
comment: Adds a relationship between a Logical Segment and the Interface between its gateway Host and the Logical Subnet it routes to.

label: LS-iH+NPE
comment: Finds a solo Logical Subnet that is not a hotspot, and creates a zero length network path for comms within the subnet, plus an NPE to generate paths finishing at that subnet.

label: OPLS1+NP
comment: Finds a zero-length Network Path and a Path Terminator (NPE) to a Logical Subnet, where there is a Logical Route via a Gateway Host to the Subnet from some other Logical Subnet, and creates a new Network Path by pre-pending the Logical Route to the previous path.

label: OPLS2+NP
comment: Finds a Network Path and terminator (NPE) to a destination Logical Subnet, where there is a Logical Route into the Subnet at the start of the Path via a Gateway, from a Subnet not visited by any shorter path to the destination, where the Path is routed via at least one Host but not via the Gateway, and creates a new Network Path by pre-pending the Logical Route to the previous path.

label: PS-iH+PPE
comment: Finds a solo Physical Subnet, and creates a zero length physical network path for comms within the subnet, plus a PPE to generate paths finishing at that subnet.

label: OPPS1+PP
comment: Finds a zero-length Physical Path and a Path Terminator (PPE) to a Physical Subnet, where there is a Logical Route via a Physical Gateway Host to the Subnet from some other Physical Subnet, and creates a new Physical Path by pre-pending the Logical Route to the previous path.

label: OPPS2+PP
comment: Finds a Physical Path and terminator (PPE) to a destination Physical Subnet, where there is a Logical Route into the Subnet at the start of the Path via a Gateway, from a Physical Subnet not visited by any shorter physical path to the destination, where the Path is routed via at least one Host but not via the Gateway, and creates a new Physical Path by pre-pending the Logical Route to the previous path.

label: NP3+x
comment: Iteratively inserts relationships between a network path and all its subpaths.

label: LPsLS+v
comment: Finds a Logical Subnet at the start of a Logical Path, and adds a link specifying that the path visits the subnet.

label: NP2LS+v
comment: Adds a visits relationship from a network path used by a service channel to a logical subnet visited by a subpath.

label: NP2LSg+t
comment: Adds a traverses relationship from a network path to a logical segment traversed by a subpath.

label: LPLS2NSg2+b
comment: Finds a route between subnets through a gateway where NAT is used on the return path, and a logical path traversing the forward segment. Adds self referential relationships marking the route and the logical path as blocked by default.

label: LPLRTSg-f+b
comment: Finds path traversing a route between subnets through a gateway which also has a tethering connection to the source subnet, but this does not route to the destination subnet, and the destination subnet is not provided by the gateway. Adds self referential relationships marking the route and the logical path as blocked by default.

label: H2dPH2+VC
comment: Finds two hosts on a virtual subnet that are on the path of a service channel, with their interfaces and their (distinct) physical hosts, and creates a virtual channel representing a dependency on physical communication between the physical hosts.

label: VCH2LS2PP+HC
comment: Finds a virtual subnet communication path between physical hosts, including the virtual channel, path generator and the start and end subnets, and inserts a host channel linked with this network path.

label: VSVCHC+v
comment: Finds a Virtual Subnet via a Virtual Channel via a Host Channel, and makes the subnet also go via the Host Channel.

label: HCLPLSg+t
comment: Finds a host channel via a physical path that traverses a logical segment, and adds the dependency to the host channel.

label: HCLPvLS+v
comment: Finds a host channel via a physical path that visits a subnet, and adds the dependency to the host channel.

label: HCLSg+vf
comment: Finds a host channel that traverses a logical segment, along with the inbound and outbound interfaces to the segment host, and adds dependencies on the outbound interface to the host channel.

label: HCLSg+vt
comment: Finds a host channel that traverses a logical segment, along with the inbound and outbound interfaces to the segment host, and adds dependencies on the inbound interface to the host channel.

label: VSVCHCLS+uPS
comment: Finds a Virtual Subnet over which interprocess communication goes on a Host Channel via a physical subnet, and adds a link denoting the dependency of the virtual subnet on the physical.

label: DFDSfP+fVP
comment: Finds a DataFlow via a DataStep from a Process, and adds a link to say the DataFlow goes via the Process.

label: DFtP+fVP
comment: Finds a DataFlow to a Process, and adds a link to say the DataFlow goes via the Process.

label: DFuCuS-C-P+u
comment: Finds a data flow via two processes, one of which is a client of the other via a transparent reverse proxy or chain of proxies, where the Client has no other client in the same chain, and the service has no other service in the same chain through which the data flows. Adds a link to specify that the client (indirectly) uses the service.

label: DFvCvS-C-P+u
comment: Finds a data flow via two processes, one of which is a client of the other via an authenticating reverse proxy or chain of proxies, where the Client has no other client in the same chain, and the service has no other service in the same chain through which the data flows. Adds a link to specify that the client (indirectly) uses the service.

label: CuvaS+u
comment: Finds a client accessing a process via an authenticating proxy. Adds a link to specify that the client uses the service indirectly.

label: CuPaS-i+i
comment: Finds a Client using a Service via an authenticating reverse Proxy that also uses the Service via an authenticating proxy, where the Proxy doesn't yet have an indirect usage link to the Service, and adds this link.

label: CScP-v+AA
comment: Finds a client using a service not via an authenticating proxy, where the service is controlled by another process that is not itself used by the service, i.e. the process is an authenticator. Adds indirect usage relationships.

label: CuPvnS+n
comment: Finds a client using a service via an authentication proxy (i.e. the proxy forwards credentials as well as other requests), and adds links to say the back end service handles authentication for the proxy.

label: CuS-SP+CC
comment: Adds a Client Channel between a Client and Service that communicate directly (not via a proxy).

label: CSL0H+SC
comment: Finds a client channel whose client and service are collocated on a host that is not a cluster, and an internal (socket) LAN provided by the host accessible in a space, and inserts a service channel between client and service via the socket LAN.

label: CSL3H+SC
comment: Finds a client channel whose client and service are collocated on a cluster host that is accessible in a space, and an L3 Subnet connecting to the cluster, and inserts a service channel between client and service via the Subnet.

label: CSL1H2+SC
comment: Finds a client and service whose hosts are paired, and creates a service channel via the pair.

label: CSLSH2-SC+SC
comment: Finds a client and service on different hosts connected to the same subnet that is not a hotspot, and adds a service channel on the zero-length path via the common subnet.

label: CSLS2H2-SC+SC
comment: Finds a client and service between which there is as yet no service channel, running on different unpaired hosts connected to different logical subnets that are not hotspots, connected by a network path in which neither host is a gateway, and adds a service channel between client and service.

label: SCLPLSg+t
comment: Finds a service channel via a logical path that traverses a logical segment, and adds the dependency to the service channel.

label: SCLPvLS+v
comment: Finds a service channel via a logical path that visits a subnet, adds a link to say the service channel also visits that subnet.

label: SCLSg+vf
comment: Finds a service channel that traverses a logical segment, along with the inbound and outbound interfaces to the segment host, and adds dependencies on the outbound interface to the service channel.

label: SCLSg+vt
comment: Finds a service channel that traverses a logical segment, along with the inbound and outbound interfaces to the segment host, and adds dependencies on the inbound interface to the service channel.

label: SC4HVSVC+vVC
comment: Finds a Service Channel crossing a Virtual Subnet between two Hosts, and the Virtual Channel representing the physical connectivity requirement to support this communication, and adds a dependency between the Service Channel and this Virtual Channel.

label: SC4HVSHC+vHC
comment: Finds a Service Channel crossing a Virtual Subnet between two Hosts, and the Host Channel representing a physical network path supporting this communication, and adds a dependency between the Service Channel and this Host Channel.

label: SCNSg+vS
comment: Finds a Service Channel that traverses a NAT segment, and adds a link to specify that source addresses in the subnet before the segment cannot be distinguished from the client source address.

label: SCLSgvTS-vS+vS
comment: Finds a service channel traversing a logical segment, where the subnet after the segment has source addresses that cannot be distinguished from a client source address, and adds a link to indicate the same must be true of the subnet before the segment.

label: SCvLS-vS+fS
comment: Finds a service channel that visits a Logical Subnet, and there is no relationship indicating that source addresses cannot be distinguished from a client, and adds a relationship indicating that they can.

label: SCLSgfTS+lI
comment: Finds a Service Channel traversing a NAT segment (with its interfaces) after which source addresses can be distinguished from a client, and adds the outbound interface from the segment as the last interface for the Service Channel

label: SCCHNPLS-lI+lI
comment: Finds a Service Channel via a Logical Path from a Client, the Client Host, Subnet and Interface, where the Service Channel has no last interface, and sets this to the client interface.

label: CCSC+ch
comment: Adds a relationship between client and service channels between the same pair of processes.

label: CCSCvLS+vLS
comment: Finds a Client Channel via a Service Channel that visits a Logical Subnet, and inserts the same relationship from the Client Channel.

label: CCSCfI+fI
comment: Finds a Client Channel via a Service Channel that goes from an Interface, and inserts the same relationship from the Client Channel.

label: CCSCtI+tI
comment: Finds a Client Channel via a Service Channel that goes to an Interface, and inserts the same relationship from the Client Channel.

label: CCSCvI+vI
comment: Finds a Client Channel via a Service Channel that goes via an Interface, and inserts the same relationship from the Client Channel.

label: CCSCtSg+tSg
comment: Finds a Client Channel via a Service Channel that goes via a Logical Segment, and inserts the same relationship from the Client Channel.

label: CCSCVC+ch
comment: Finds a Client Channel via a Service Channel via a Virtual Channel, and adds the Virtual Channel dependency to the Client Channel.

label: CCSCHC+ch
comment: Finds a Client Channel via a Service Channel via a Host Channel, and adds the Host Channel dependency to the Client Channel.

label: CuvS+CC
comment: Finds a client using a process via a proxy and adds a client channel representing their trust relationship.

label: CuPuSCC+c
comment: Finds a client accessing a process that is acting as an authentication proxy and accessing a service, including the indirect usage link from client to service, and the associated client channels. Adds dependency links between the client channels.

label: CuPvSCC+c
comment: Finds a client accessing a process that is acting as an authentication proxy and indirectly accessing a service, including the indirect usage link from client to service, and the associated client channels. Adds dependency links between the client channels.

label: CvPuSCC+c
comment: Finds a client indirectly accessing a process that is acting as an authentication proxy and accessing a service, including the indirect usage link from client to service, and the associated client channels. Adds dependency links between the client channels.

label: CvPvSCC+c
comment: Finds a client indirectly accessing a service via a chain of authentication proxies, including two adjacent proxies in the chain, the indirect usage link from client to service, and the associated client channels. Adds dependency links between the client channels.

label: CCCvCCvLS+vLS
